TASK: Fix the top 3 crash risks identified in the WibWob-DOS TUI when rapidly spawning and closing windows via IPC. Apply these fixes:

FIX 1 — Leaked timer in TRoomInputView (room_chat_view.cpp)
The blink timer is never killed on destruction. Add a destructor (or modify the existing one) that calls killTimer() on the blink timer handle before the view is destroyed. Look at how other views handle timer cleanup for the pattern.

FIX 2 — Force-destroy in api_close_window (wwdos_app.cpp around line 3263)
The current code does w->close() then immediately remove+destroy if the window is still present. This violates deferred-close contracts. Change it to:
- Call w->close() 
- If the window handles close gracefully (removes itself), done
- Only force-remove+destroy if the window is still in the desktop AND does not have a deferred close flag
- Add a comment explaining the two-phase approach

FIX 3 — Mark internal-only windows as non-spawnable
In window_type_registry.cpp, the "wibwob" entry has a spawn function but is meant to be internal-only (comment says so). Set its spawn function to nullptr so get_window_types reports spawnable:false. Same for "scramble" if it has a spawn function. The smoke test should not be able to spawn these.

IMPORTANT:
- Do NOT change any file outside of app/ directory
- Do NOT modify any test files
- Keep changes minimal and surgical
- Make sure the code compiles (check includes are correct)
- Use the existing code style (no modernisms like std::unique_ptr unless already used nearby)
